TY  - JOUR
T1  - Modeling a Phone Center: Analysis of a Multichannel, Multiresource Processor Shared Loss System
AU  - Akşin, O. Zeynep
AU  - Harker, Patrick T.
Y1  - 2001/02/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.47.2.324.9842
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.47.2.324.9842
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 324
EP  - 336
VL  - 47
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper presents a model for the study of operations at an inbound call center. The call center is modeled as a multiclass processor shared loss system, where the interacting effects of human, telecommunication, and information technology resources are explicitly incorporated. Product form solutions and approximations for this type of system are provided along with expressions for performance measures like blocking and reneging. Some structural properties of system throughput are analyzed in an effort to pave the way for future optimization studies dealing with the design and management of phone centers.
AB  - This paper presents a model for the study of operations at an inbound call center. The call center is modeled as a multiclass processor shared loss system, where the interacting effects of human, telecommunication, and information technology resources are explicitly incorporated. Product form solutions and approximations for this type of system are provided along with expressions for performance measures like blocking and reneging. Some structural properties of system throughput are analyzed in an effort to pave the way for future optimization studies dealing with the design and management of phone centers.
